\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 APPENDIX: THE 14 WORDS NEVER TO USE}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par Sometimes it is not what you say that matters but what you don\rquote t say. Other times a single word or phrase can undermine or destroy the credibility of a para
graph or entire presentation. This memo was originally prepared exclusively for Congressional spouses because they are your eyes and ears, a one-person reality check and truth squad combined. However, by popular demand, I have included and expanded that d
ocument because effectively communicating requires you to STOP saying words and phrases that undermine your ability to educate the American people.
\par So from today forward, YOU are the language police. From today forward, these are the words never to say again.
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 1. Government - Washington}{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par NEVER SAY: Government \line INSTEAD SAY: Washington}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par The fact is, most Americans appreciate their local government that picks up their trash, cleans their streets, and provides police and transportation services. Washington is the p
roblem. Remind voters again and again about Washington spending, Washington waste, Washington taxation, Washington bureaucracy, Washington rules and Washington regulations. Then remind voters that if Washington created this mess, it is 
\par Washington\rquote s respon
sibility to fix it. "If we expect to succee4 we must look to ourselves and not to Washington to raise our kids, start our businesses and improve our day-to-day lives." If you must talk about government, use the context defined by President Bush: "Governme
nt should help people improve their lives) not try to run their lives.
\par }{\f37\fs17\insrsid16203692 \page }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 2. Privatization/Private Accounts - Personalization/Personal Accounts}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Privatization/Private Accounts\line INSTEAD SAY: Personalization/Personal Accounts}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par Many more Americans would
 "personalize" Social Security than "privatize" it. In fact, two-thirds of America want to personalize Social Security while only one-third would privatize it. Why? Personalizing Social Security suggests ownership and control over your retirement savings,
 while privatizing it suggests a profit motive and winners and losers, BANISH PRIVATIZATION FROM YOUR LEXICON.
\par }{\b\i\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 PAGE 157 ---}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 3 Tax Reform - Tax Simplification }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Tax Reform\line INSTEAD SAY: Tax Simplification}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par While a majority of Americans are generally 
in favor of tax reform, one-third of the population fears that they would end up paying more in taxes if the tax code was in fact reformed. However, almost all Americans believe they would personally benefit from a tax code that was simplified -- in terms
 of money they owe, time they spend and anxiety about the IRS. When more Americans fear the IRS than root-canal surgery, something should be done to simplify the tax code. 
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 4. Inheritance/Estate Tax - The Death Tax }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Inheritance/Estate Tax\line INSTEAD SAY: The Death Tax}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par While a sizeable 68% of America thinks the Inheritance/Estate Tax is unfair, fully 78% think that the Death Tax is unfair. And while a narrow majority would repeal the inheritance/estate tax, an overwhelming majority would repeal the d
eath tax. If you want to kill the estate tax, call it a death tax.
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 5. A Global Economy/Globalization/Capitalism - Free Market Economy}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Global Economy/Globalization/Capitalism\line INSTEAD SAY: Free Market Economy}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par More Americans are afraid of the prin
ciple of globalization than even privatization. The reason? Globalization represents something big, something distant and something foreiwi. it.s the same reason why Americans like their local government but dislike Washington -- the closer you are, the m
o
re control you have. So instead of talking about the principles of globalization, instead emphasize "the value and benefits of a free market economy." Similarly, capitalism reminds people of harsh economic competition that yields losers as well as winners
. Conversely, the free market economy provides opportunity to all and allows everyone to succeed.
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 6. Outsourcing - Taxation, Regulation, Litigation, Innovation, Education }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Outsourcing\line INSTEAD SAY: Taxation, Regulation, Litigation, Innovation, Education}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par When you use the words of your oppositions you are basically accepting their definition and therefore their conclusion. We should NEVER use the word outsourcing because we will then be asked to defend or end the practice of allowing companies to shi
p American jobs overseas. Rather, we should talk about the "root cause" why any company would not want to hire "the best workers in the world." And the answer: "over-taxation, over-regulation, too much litigation, and not enough innovation or quality educ
ation." Because it rhymes, it will be remembered. 
\par }{\b\i\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 PAGE 158 ---}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957  
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 7. Undocumented Workers - Illegal Aliens}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Undocumented Workers\line INSTEAD SAY: Illegal Aliens}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par The Dems have adopted the phrase "undocumented worker" but you shouldn\rquote t. Call them exactly
 what they are. In fact, instead of addressing "immigration reform, "which polarizes Americans, you should be talking about "border security" issues. Securing our borders and our people has universal support.
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 8. Foreign Trade - International Trade}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Foreign Trade\line INSTEAD SAY: International Trade}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par For many reasons unrelated to this issue, the word "foreign" conjures up negative images. Americans simply don\rquote t like "foreign oil," or "foreign products" or "foreign nationals." International is a more po
sitive concept than either foreign or global.
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 9. Drilling for oil - Exploring for energy}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Drilling for oil\line INSTEAD SAY: Exploring for energy}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par It\rquote s the picture people paint in their minds, the difference between an old-fashioned oilrig that gushes
 up black goop vs. 21st Century technology and innovation that provides us the ability to heat our homes and drive our cars. When you talk about energy, use words like "responsible" and "balanced" and always address your concern for the environment.

\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 10. Tort Reform - Lawsuit Abuse Reform}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Tort Reform\line INSTEAD SAY: Lawsuit Abuse Reform}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par The term "tort" has very little meaning to the average American, and at best reminds one of a French pastry. "Lawsuit Abuse" is something most Americans understand and resent. If you really want to make your case, add the word "frivolous."
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 11. Trial Lawyer - Personal Injury Lawyer }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Trial Lawyer\line INSTEAD SAY: Personal Injury Lawyer}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par It is hard to distrust a trial lawyer because we see them portrayed so favora
bly on L.A. Law and Law & Order. But personal injury lawyers, also known as ambulance chasers, remind people of those annoying, harassing commercials we see at 1:00 am cajoling us to sue someone. If you want to get the frill bang for the buck, call them "
predatory personal injury lawyers." 
