\par }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 12. Corporate Transparency - Corporate Accountability }{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: Corporate Transparency\line INSTEAD SAY: Corporate Accountability}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par I constantly hear the need for "transparency" coming from members of the financi
al services industry as well as Members of Congress. But if you asked the American people, corporate accountability is a much higher priority. The fact is, a majority of Americans can\rquote 
t even explain what transparency actually means. But everyone understands and demands accountability from all sectors of the economy ... and the government. 
\par \line }{\b\f37\fs17\ul\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 13. School Choice - Parental Choice/Equal Opportunity in Education}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par }{\b\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 NEVER SAY: School Choice\line INSTEAD SAY: Parental Choice/Equal Opportunity in Education}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
\par Americans are still evenly split over whether they support "school choice" in America\rquote s schools. But they are heavily in favor of "giving parents the right to choose th}{\f37\fs17\insrsid16203692 e}{\f37\fs17\insrsid8734957\charrsid8734957 
 schools that are right for their children," and there is almost universal support for "equal opportunity in education." So frame the issue right and you get the support you need.
